# Bias Audit Pipeline — Research Goal

This project aims to **write a research paper on how bias is introduced into modern AI systems**, with a focus on **financial AI**, and to **technically prove the findings** in the research paper.

When editing this codebase:

- Keep the research paper as the primary deliverable; agents and outputs should support that goal.
- Ensure technical proofs (metrics, experiments, figures) are reproducible and correctly documented.
- Bias detection and mitigation should align with EU AI Act fairness thresholds and established fairness metrics (DPD, EOD, disparate impact).
- Use original wording from reference PDFs (bias_mitigation.pdf, Bias Auditing Framework.pdf, Bias Detection findings.pdf) when possible; only reword when content is duplicated across sources (Gemini decides).
- Ensure all topics from the three reference PDFs are mentioned in the paper; the topic_coverage_agent verifies this.
- Everything we do should move towards a unified agentic system to produce the paper backed up by facts.
